<TITLE> Full-time medical care for Hasina: official </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 18 (bdnews24.com) Detained Awami League chief Sheikh Hasina will be provided with full-time medical care, inspector general (prisons) Brigadier General Md Zakir Hasan said Wednesday. The health ministry took the initiative following requests from the jail authorities. Zakir told bdnews24.com that facilities like a full-time doctor, a nurse and an ambulance would be provided for the AL chief. Doctors examined Hasina Tuesday and Wednesday in the special jail. She was also given physiotherapy Tuesday upon her request, the AL chief's special assistant Dr Hasan Mahmud said. An appointed doctor will be examining Hasina from Thursday, according to the directives of the health ministry. Security forces arrested Hasina at her Sudha Sadan home in an extortion case on July 16 and a Dhaka court sent her to jail, rejecting a prayer for bail the same day. bdnews
